ENTRY            L0290   20260219   20260422   20260422       L057
SUBENT        L0290001   20260219   20260422   20260422       L057
BIB                 12         80
TITLE      Photonuclear cross sections for 197Au: An update on
           the gold standard
AUTHOR     (J.Song,D.Rotsch,J.A.Nolen,R.Gampa,R.M.de Kruijff,
           T.Brossard,C.R.Howell,F.Krishichayan,Y.K.Wu,
           S.Mikhailov,M.W.Ahmed,R.V.F.Janssens)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,110,064604,2024)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.110.064604
INSTITUTE  (1USAANL,1USAORL,1USADKE,1USATNL,1USANCC,1USANCA)
FACILITY   (LASER,1USATNL) The Triangle Universities Nuclear
           Laboratory's (TUNL) High-Intensity Gamma-Ray Source
            (HIgS).
INC-SPECT  Beam irradiation and intensities with associated
           one sigma uncertainties:
           -------------------------------------------------------
           Egamma   Irradiation time         Intensity     Unc.
           -------------------------------------------------------
           MeV            hr               10**8 gamma/s   %
           -------------------------------------------------------
           14            11.49                 8.01       8.2
           16            10.72                 8.80       8.2
           18             8.17                 9.27       8.2
           22            10.73                 2.48       8.2
           24            11.20                 2.70       8.2
           27            11.73                 2.51       8.2
           31             9.12                 2.06       8.2
           -------------------------------------------------------
DETECTOR   (HPGE) After activation, gamma-ray spectra were
           measured with 12 high purity germanium (HPGe)
           detectors, each with a coaxial cylindrical crystal
           positioned with its front face 5 cm from the
           activated target.
SAMPLE     The target stack was composed of layers of Au, TiO2,
           Zn, Os, and Au. Target stacks and thicknesses:
           -------------------------------------------------------
           Egamma (MeV)           14,27      16,24      18,22,31
           -------------------------------------------------------
           tgt.thick. seg.       (g/cm2)    (g/cm2)    (g/cm2)
           -------------------------------------------------------
           1 197Au    1          0.681      0.713      0.763
                      2          0.931      0.933      0.655
                      3          1.033      0.935      0.869
           2 TiO2     1          0.228      0.241      0.235
                      2          0.205      0.194      0.163
                      3          0.205      0.220      0.221
           3 Zn       1          0.501      0.350      0.308
                      2          0.392      0.292      0.363
                      3          0.351      0.339      0.406
           4 Os       1          0.304      0.293      0.358
                      2          0.257      0.242      0.220
                      3          0.614      0.553      0.362
           5 197Au    1          1.209      1.299      1.115
                      2          0.834      1.195      1.049
                      3          1.304      1.395      1.471
           -------------------------------------------------------
METHOD     (ACTIV) A new target activation method that is based
           on the angle-energy correlation of the laser
           Compton-scattered photon beams at the High Intensity
           Gamma-ray Source (HIgS).
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) The total error include statistical, and
           three and three systematic errors for the gamma-ray
           branching ratio, detector efficiency and beam flux.
           The total experimental error can be obtained by:
           dsigma = sqrt[(dN/N)**2 + (dI0/I0)**2 +
            (depsilon/epsilon)**2 + (dIbr/Ibr)**2], where dN,
           dI0, depsilon, and dIbr are uncertainties from the
           number of nuclei measured by gamma counts, photon beam
           flux, HPGe detector efficiency, and the gamma branching
            ratio of the selected nuclei, respectively.
           (ERR-1) Photon beam flux.
CORRECTION The total correction factor call is expressed as call
           = c*cDT*cbr*cba*csab. The c, cDT, cbr, cba, and csab
           symbols are corrections for the detector efficiency,
           detector dead time during the measurements, gamma-ray
           branching ratio, gamma-ray beam attenuation, and
           self-absorption by passing through the targets,
           respectively. Correction of the primary photon beam
           flux due to attenuation and of the emitted gamma-ray
           yield from Au isotopes due to self-absorption are
           taken into account.
HISTORY    (20260219C) BP
ENDBIB              80
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
        8.2
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           87
